results.name: Expansion of Product_{m>=1} (1+q^m)^(-16).
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
formula: a(0) = 1, a(n) = -(16/n)*Sum_{k=1..n} A000593(k)*a(n-k) for n > 0. - _Seiichi Manyama_, Apr 05 2017
mathematica: nmax = 50; CoefficientList[Series[Product[1/(1 + x^k)^16, {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 27 2015 *)
